const body = "\n\n\n## Introduction\n\nOver the past few years, the B2B marketplace is catching on to the digital trend by placing itself to be the main storefront. Although retail space has quickly picked up an e-commerce business, the B2B food marketplace is gradually following their footsteps. When it comes to innovation, there is so much scope for B2B marketplaces to thrive. An increasing number of B2B businesses (manufacturers, distributors, wholesalers, etc) have uncovered that the digital marketplace business model is crucial for their expansion.\n\nThere is cutthroat competition with all the business owners shifting towards digital platforms, businesses are in a dire need of someone who can narrow the gap with distributors, negotiate commercials, and place orders.\n\n### DECODING B2B MARKETPLACE\nB2B marketplaces is an online marketplace trading of products and services between businesses. They provide a platform over which manufacturers, distributors, and suppliers deal with buying and selling of raw materials, end products, or services. They simplify everything related to purchasing.\n\nTypically there are 3 principal actors in a B2B marketplace: Buyer, seller, and marketplace owners. All the actor’s leverage on benefits such as greater market reach cost savings and streamlined workflows.\n\n### WHY THE NEED TO GO DIGITAL?\nGoing digital gives buyers the power over a wide array of products, lower transaction costs, price transparency and comparison to make better financial decisions, a simple and easy buying process, and of course a better purchasing experience. A streamlined digital platform elevates collaboration between buyers and sellers and forms better relationships with clients. By going online, businesses can showcase their products and customize them according to customer segments and demand requirements.\n\nIt is imperative to establish strong relationships on e-platform so that businesses can increase procurement, enhance delivery speed and scale down costs involved. Manufacturers and suppliers upsell products to their buyers. When the system is transparent, there is clear visibility with real-time tracking to guarantee on-time delivery. Even after the order has been delivered, customers can report any discrepancy or quality mismatch.\n\n### How to Start an online B2B Marketplace?\nWe have outlined a few things you need to know to establish an online marketplace:\n\n- **Ideation**\n\nThis is the core step to get your B2B to trend online. You need to decide what type of online platform whether a website or app or both meets your business model. Determine how you can be the solution provider by going online. Additionally, evaluate market trends and your competitors. Secure your strong points and innovate how you can better serve your customers.\n\n- **Designing**\n\nDo the groundwork of market research reports, industry needs, technical requirements, customer insights, the features you want to integrate, whether you want to go digital using an internal team or outsourcing to industry experts.\n\n- **Development**\n\nIt entirely depends upon your business requirements, either you can develop the platform from scratch or leverage on customizing ready-to-use platforms.\n\n### TOP 10 FEATURES OF AN ONLINE B2B MARKETPLACE\n\n- **Product management**\n\nThis feature aids in generating more sales and eliminates common issues like erroneous product description, pricing mismatch etc.\n\n- **Managed Profiles**\n\nBuyers and Sellers should have access to easy navigation, search filters, detailed information about buyers/sellers, orders placed, history and shipment tracking etc.\n\n- **Call to Action button**\n\nIt is a vital option for lead generation to drive better conversion rate. Achieve desired results by artfully placing CTA buttons.\n\n- **Intelligent filters**\n\nAdvanced filters help ease the buyer’s journey to better search products by bifurcating search parameters on the basis of cost, location, type etc.\n\n- **Vendor management**\n\nWith the help of the system, gather all your vendor’s data on the same system. Use a CRM system to build a good relationship with them.\n\n- **Blending with all system**\n\nEvery business has multiple systems taking care of their business operations. Your platform should blend with all those systems and give enhanced experience to users.\n\n- **Instant Communication**\n\nFor faster operations, there should be an option of buyers directly communicating with sellers or vice-versa. This not only ensures smooth processes but ensures transparency.\n\n- **Streamlined payment options**\n\nUsers should be able to pay with multiple payment gateways options instantly and at the same time in a safe and secure manner with a mutually decided payment option.\n\n- **Consolidated Data**\n\nAll your data needs to be consolidated and managed on a single platform to drive insights from those data points to know the advancement of your business.\n\n\n### CHALLENGES FACED BY ONLINE B2B MARKETPLACE\nFew of the challenges faced are:\n\n- **Tie up with clients**\n\nYour business is nothing without maintaining cordial relationships with your clients. One mistake and you can lose a potential customer base. To avoid this, integrate your digital platform with the CRM system for better association with your clients.\n\n- **Order management**\n\nBe prepared for orders of any size, whether small or huge. Manage your inventory accordingly, use a proactive approach.\n\n- **Technological development**\n\nInvest in any technology that is adaptable to any business changes that you can face even in the future.\n\nEvery benefit of going digital, comes with its unique challenges, however choosing the right partner for your online B2B business can help overcome these challenges.\n\nB2B marketplaces are not one size fits all types of business. NestorBird understands every business has its unique way of operating even in complex business situations. Kickstart your B2B business because we will do everything for you.\n\n\n[Get A Free Consultation](/contact-us)";
